text.section:
Any political subdivision that acquires, leases, controls, or sets apart any property for an airport, airport facility, or air navigation facility may:
Establish and operate the airport or facility;
Lease or grant to any person, on the terms and conditions it considers proper, any right or interest in the airport or facility;
Fix any charges, rentals, or fees for the use of the airport or facility and for any right or interest granted to any person under this section; and
Delegate any of its powers under this section to any suitable officer or agency of the political subdivision and, for this purpose, create any new agency or unit.
